
Managing users and groups:

   
   • useradd -m -G wheel -s /bin/bash <newuser>  - creates a new user 
    
           -m  - automatically creates a home directory for the user
           -G  - adds the user to the wheel group as a supplementary group. wheel allows for sudo priveledges.
           -s  - specifies the shell as bash.


   • passwd <username> - adds a password for the user's account


   • userdel -r <username>  - deletes a user, and the group created on it's formation.

           -r  - deletes the user's home directory


    
